Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once the pan is hot, add the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} and @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}.

Fry until both the bacon and sausage have browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly. Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the sausage.

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Once the meat is browned, stir in the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, carrot, @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, then pop a #lid on the pan (or cover with #foil) and bake on the middle shelf of your #oven until the meat is tender and the sauce has thickened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When there are 15 mins of ragu cooking time left, bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

When boiling, add the @Spaghetti{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Remove the ragu from the #oven, stir in the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g}, cooked pasta, @Butter{20%g} and half of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}.

Taste and season with @salt and @ground black pepper if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} to loosen the sauce if you'd like.

Divide your ragu al forno pasta between your serving bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!